{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"writevAsync"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"vectors"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GOutputVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"nVectors"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ioPriority","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"callback","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GAsyncReadyCallback","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GAsyncReadyCallback"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil, "},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"During an async request no other sync and async calls are allowed,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and will result in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pending"},{"type":"text","text":" errors."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On success, the number of bytes written will be passed to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"text":". It is not an error if this is not the same as the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requested size, as it can happen e.g. on a partial I\/O error,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but generally we try to write as many bytes as requested."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You are guaranteed that this method will never fail with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"wouldBlock","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stream"},{"text":" can’t accept more data, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"method will just wait until this changes.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Any outstanding I\/O request with higher priority (lower numerical","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"value) will be executed before an outstanding request with lower"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"priority. Default priority is [PRIORITY_DEFAULT](\/\/documentation\/glib\/priority_default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The asynchronous methods have a default fallback that uses threads"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to implement asynchronicity, so they are optional for inheriting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"classes. However, if you override one you must override all."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the synchronous, blocking version of this function, see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_output_stream_writev()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that no copy of "},{"code":"vectors","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be made, so it must stay valid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"until ","type":"text"},{"type"